SIMPLE: honestly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honestly
<hw>Hon"est*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Honorably; becomingly; decently.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In an honest manner; <as>as, a contract
<ex>honestly</ex> made; to live <ex>honestly</ex>; to speak
<ex>honestly</ex>.</as></def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To come honestly by</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>To get
honestly.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A circumlocution for <xex>to
inherit</xex>; as, <xex>to come honestly by</xex> a feature, a mental
trait, a peculiarity.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honesty</ent>⟦br⟧
